Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of affray. I would like to take this opportunity to provide some context to the events that unfolded that night.

Emotions were running high as I had just learned of my boyfriend's infidelity. In a moment of anger and hurt, I made the regrettable decision to confront him at the bar where he was with his friends. However, I want to make it clear that my intentions were never to cause physical harm. I simply wanted answers and closure.

During my time at the bar, I admit that my emotions got the better of me, resulting in me raising my voice and making threats. I must emphasize that these were empty threats, as I never possessed nor had any means of obtaining a firearm. Unfortunately, my words caused distress among the other patrons present, and for that, I deeply apologize.

It is important to note that prior to this incident, I have maintained a clean criminal record. I have always strived to be a law-abiding citizen and contribute positively to society. In fact, I attend therapy sessions once a week to address my own personal issues and work on self-improvement.

I stand here today to express my remorse for my actions and to acknowledge the need for better judgment in handling difficult situations. I understand that my behavior at the bar was unacceptable and that there were alternative ways to seek resolution.

I assure the court that I have taken this incident as a stark reminder of the need for personal growth and self-control. I am committed to learning from this experience and taking the necessary steps to prevent any similar occurrences in the future.

In mitigation, I ask the court to consider my guilty plea as a genuine act of remorse and acceptance of responsibility for my actions. I have already begun the process of personal development and I am willing to continue therapy as a means of self-improvement.

While I acknowledge the impact my behavior had on those present at the bar, I have already suffered the consequences of my actions. The realization of the fear and discomfort I caused has been a heavy burden to bear.

Your Honor, I humbly request your leniency, considering my lack of criminal history, my willingness to address my personal issues, and my sincere remorse for the distress I caused. I am determined to make amends and become a better member of society.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to express myself and for considering the circumstances surrounding this regrettable incident.

