Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, plead guilty to the offense of affray. I fully acknowledge and accept the gravity of my plea and the significance that it carries. Through this guilty plea, I take complete responsibility for my actions and express genuine remorse for the distress I caused.

On the night in question, I had just discovered my boyfriend's infidelity, which caused me intense emotional turmoil. Overwhelmed by a mixture of anger and hurt, I made the unfortunate decision to confront him at the bar where he was socializing with his friends. In hindsight, I now realize that my behavior was inappropriate and unacceptable.

During the confrontation, I raised my voice and, with deep regret, made an empty threat about obtaining a gun. I must emphasize that I do not, and have never, possessed a firearm nor have any means of obtaining one. My intent was solely to express my emotional pain, though I understand the fear and distress my words may have caused to those present.

In addition to raising my voice, I also resorted to slapping my boyfriend across the face in a moment of heated emotions. However, I did not cause any further harm and deeply regret my actions.

Today, I stand before you with utmost sincerity and genuine remorse for the disruption and fear I caused to the patrons in the bar. This incident has taught me a valuable lesson about controlling my emotions and handling difficult situations in a more appropriate manner.

Your Honor, I humbly request leniency and understanding as I take full responsibility for my actions. I am committed to learning from this experience and working on improving myself. I understand the consequences of my guilty plea, and I am prepared to face them as I strive to become a better person.

Respectfully,
Chloe Mills

