1180
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, plead guilty to the offense of affray. I fully acknowledge and accept the gravity of my plea and the significance that it carries. Through this guilty plea, I take complete responsibility for my actions and express genuine remorse for the distress I caused.

On the night in question, I had just found out that my boyfriend cheated on me. Overwhelmed by anger and hurt, I went to the bar where I knew he was with his friends. During the confrontation, I threatened to get a gun and shoot him if he did not tell me the name of the other girl, even though I don't own a gun or have any means of obtaining one. I deeply regret using such threats to express my emotional pain.

While at the bar, I slapped him in the face, but I did not cause any further harm. I understand that my actions were inappropriate and unacceptable.

I want to express my sincere apologies to everyone present at the bar for scaring them with my behavior. In retrospect, I realize that I should have handled the situation in a better, more composed manner. This incident has taught me a valuable lesson about controlling my emotions and handling difficult situations more appropriately.

Your Honor, I humbly request your leniency and understanding as I take full responsibility for my actions. I am committed to learning from this experience and working on improving myself. I already attend therapy once a week to address and better understand my emotions.

Respectfully,
Chloe Mills

